result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyara Alyse Tollan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kyara Alyse Tollan is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kyara Alyse Tollan was found guilty of Failure to Disclose Event Affecting Eligibility (>$1000<=$2000) [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.93(3)(a).
  • Kyara Alyse Tollan was found guilty of Theft-W/o Full Legal Interest <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(c).

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes, DF ATTY: Alex Andrea, DF: Kyara Alyse Tollan appeared.  Court called at 11:13 a.m.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  State moves to amend Ct. 1 to misdemeanor 946.93(3)(a)3e(3) (Public Benefits Fraud)   Ct. 2 to 943.201(3)(a) (Misdemeanor Theft)  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  DE pleads Guilty to the amended Ct 1 & amended Ct. 2.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjudicated guilty of the amended Ct 1 & the amended Ct. 2. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 3& Ct 4. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:



Amended Ct. 1 & Amended Ct. 2 to run concurrent to each other

S/W 2 year probation with conditions
- Probation can be transferred to Minnesota
- DE is directed to take all prescribed medications by her physician
- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Doris H.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.   
- Restitution in the amount of $6,633.22 to be paid to the Food Shelf program 
- Court costs in the amount of $486.00 and one DNA surcharge of $200 to be paid through the DOC
- DE to report to the jail to provide a DNA sample
- DE to sign up for probation today 05/10/16
- 20 days to appeal
